00:29:39.945 --> 00:29:41.143
PROFESSOR: It might well be.

00:29:41.143 --> 00:29:44.250
And I want to go back to that.

00:29:44.250 --> 00:29:49.220
So let's write down some models
that formalize a little

00:29:49.220 --> 00:29:52.090
bit the intuitions that
have already come.

00:29:52.090 --> 00:29:54.670
So let's start with the
simplest model.

00:29:54.670 --> 00:29:57.430
So the name of the game is going
to take these facts and

00:29:57.430 --> 00:29:58.600
write down a model.

00:29:58.600 --> 00:30:01.460
The simplest model, with the
fewest assumptions possible,

00:30:01.460 --> 00:30:06.200
is going to help us make
sense of the facts.

00:30:06.200 --> 00:30:11.970
So let's start with your
14.01 type of model,

00:30:11.970 --> 00:30:13.810
like a basic model.

00:30:13.810 --> 00:30:17.320
What should the model be?

00:30:17.320 --> 00:30:23.320
Suppose that you have d% risk
of default on any loan, but

00:30:23.320 --> 00:30:25.630
that's do the fact
that someone's

00:30:25.630 --> 00:30:26.840
business has collapsed.

00:30:26.840 --> 00:30:30.560
It's not that they ran away with
the money or whatever.

00:30:30.560 --> 00:30:31.680
It's just something happened.

00:30:31.680 --> 00:30:32.380
There business collapsed.

00:30:32.380 --> 00:30:33.140
They can't reimburse.

00:30:33.140 --> 00:30:34.000
So that's d%.

00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:36.710
That is observable
by everyone.

00:30:36.710 --> 00:30:40.440
And let's assume that the growth
interest rate is big R,

00:30:40.440 --> 00:30:44.000
so that's 1 plus little r.

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:47.920
And suppose that banking
or moneylending is

00:30:47.920 --> 00:30:49.325
a competitive industry.

00:30:52.880 --> 00:30:55.570
And so the moneylenders
make no profit.

00:30:55.570 --> 00:30:58.045
We're going to return to that,
whether it's a good assumption

00:30:58.045 --> 00:30:59.200
or a bad assumption.

00:30:59.200 --> 00:31:02.050
But suppose, for the moment,
that lending is

00:31:02.050 --> 00:31:03.810
a competitive industry.

00:31:03.810 --> 00:31:07.430
So we are going to use
a 0 profit condition.

00:31:07.430 --> 00:31:14.030
So the expected marginal product
of capital has to be 1

00:31:14.030 --> 00:31:17.920
minus d times R, So the
depositors, whatever you need

00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:21.430
to set to big R, such that
you're depositor are getting 1

00:31:21.430 --> 00:31:23.040
minus d times R.

00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:24.880
So this d is very high.

00:31:24.880 --> 00:31:28.940
Then you need to set a higher
interest rate, so that you can

00:31:28.940 --> 00:31:31.870
compensate your depositors.

00:31:31.870 --> 00:31:35.260
So that would be your
basic model.

00:31:35.260 --> 00:31:40.940
Now, let's look at what kind of
facts can it explain, what

00:31:40.940 --> 00:31:43.190
kind of fact can
it not explain.

00:31:43.190 --> 00:31:46.100
So we go back to the fact.

00:31:46.100 --> 00:31:48.650
Does it have anything to tell
us about formal versus

00:31:48.650 --> 00:31:49.900
informal lenders?

00:32:00.020 --> 00:32:02.120
In this model, everything
is seen, observable.

00:32:02.120 --> 00:32:05.870
So, in principle, everybody
should be able to lend to the

00:32:05.870 --> 00:32:07.726
poor, formal or informal.

00:32:07.726 --> 00:32:09.887
But this model doesn't tell us
why the banks are not able to

00:32:09.887 --> 00:32:11.137
lend to the poor.

00:32:14.280 --> 00:32:16.140
Can it explain high
interest rates?

00:32:16.140 --> 00:32:17.800
And under what conditions
would it explain

00:32:17.800 --> 00:32:19.050
high interest rates?

00:32:22.918 --> 00:32:24.846
AUDIENCE: If under the
assumption that the poor

00:32:24.846 --> 00:32:27.898
default more often than the
rich, then it would make sense

00:32:27.898 --> 00:32:29.680
to charge them a higher
interest rate

00:32:29.680 --> 00:32:30.190
PROFESSOR: Exactly.

00:32:30.190 --> 00:32:35.050
If the default rate was very
high, you would explain the

00:32:35.050 --> 00:32:37.200
high interest rates.

00:32:37.200 --> 00:32:41.205
And if they were differently
high for the poor than for the

00:32:41.205 --> 00:32:43.320
rich, you would also explain
that the interest rate paid by

00:32:43.320 --> 00:32:45.460
the rich is higher
than the poor.

00:32:45.460 --> 00:32:48.070
So the problem is that you can't
both explain the high

00:32:48.070 --> 00:32:51.910
interest rates and the
low default rate.

00:32:51.910 --> 00:32:53.960
Given the low default rate,
you should have

00:32:53.960 --> 00:32:56.030
low interest rates.

00:32:56.030 --> 00:32:59.160
Likewise, given the low and
reasonably similar default

00:32:59.160 --> 00:33:02.110
rate, there is no reason
for the interest

00:33:02.110 --> 00:33:03.520
rate to be very variable.

00:33:07.300 --> 00:33:10.660
The interest rate paid by
everyone should be the same.

00:33:10.660 --> 00:33:13.580
And there is no reason
for the rich to be

00:33:13.580 --> 00:33:14.700
able to borrow more.

00:33:14.700 --> 00:33:16.560
You should be able to borrow
what you need to borrow, as

00:33:16.560 --> 00:33:18.710
long as you're willing
to reimburse.

00:33:18.710 --> 00:33:22.690
And you should also not be
a lower interest rate.

00:33:22.690 --> 00:33:24.180
So that's kind or a long winded

00:33:24.180 --> 00:33:26.300
answer to your question.

00:33:26.300 --> 00:33:30.590
Even if the cost of fund is--
maybe the poor want less money

00:33:30.590 --> 00:33:33.060
because they have smaller
projects.

00:33:33.060 --> 00:33:36.980
But in that case, if the only
problem is the cost of fund

00:33:36.980 --> 00:33:40.400
multiplied by some chance of
default, then that really

00:33:40.400 --> 00:33:42.640
shouldn't fit the facts.

00:33:42.640 --> 00:33:45.320
So we need to introduce
something else to make sense

00:33:45.320 --> 00:33:45.980
of this fact.

00:33:45.980 --> 00:33:48.182
So I'm going to do
it in two steps.

00:33:48.182 --> 00:33:52.460
First, I'm going to introduce
the possibility that the

00:33:52.460 --> 00:33:56.010
borrower might want to run
away with the money.

00:33:56.010 --> 00:34:00.040
So they have invested in their
little enterprise.

00:34:00.040 --> 00:34:01.650
Their enterprise succeeded.

00:34:01.650 --> 00:34:06.250
But still they managed to
escape with the money.

00:34:06.250 --> 00:34:11.460
So imagine that the bank or the
moneylender lends to an

00:34:11.460 --> 00:34:16.850
entrepreneur who has a business,
which will lead the

00:34:16.850 --> 00:34:23.170
F of k, when k units of
capital are invested.

00:34:23.170 --> 00:34:25.489
So you invest k and
you get F of k.

00:34:25.489 --> 00:34:28.340
So supposing you have a little
shop, and you build some

00:34:28.340 --> 00:34:29.850
shelves, and you start
your business, and

00:34:29.850 --> 00:34:32.389
you'll get F of k.

00:34:32.389 --> 00:34:36.110
So if you already have w, in
order to invest k, you need to

00:34:36.110 --> 00:34:39.460
borrow k minus w, right?

00:34:39.460 --> 00:34:41.790
And then at the end of the
period, you need to reimburse

00:34:41.790 --> 00:34:45.790
k minus w, multiplied by the
growth interest rate, what

00:34:45.790 --> 00:34:47.130
you've borrowed plus
the interest rate

00:34:47.130 --> 00:34:50.280
on what you've borrowed.

00:34:50.280 --> 00:34:53.679
Everyone's on board with that?

00:34:53.679 --> 00:34:57.830
So if we didn't have the chance
that people run away

00:34:57.830 --> 00:35:00.350
with the money, we
would be done.

00:35:00.350 --> 00:35:05.580
Now, suppose that you could
spend some cost, h, and then

00:35:05.580 --> 00:35:07.300
you could run away
with the money.

00:35:07.300 --> 00:35:10.690
And suppose that spending the
cost, h, is not on the amount

00:35:10.690 --> 00:35:12.880
of money you've borrowed, but on
the entire amount of money

00:35:12.880 --> 00:35:14.420
you've invested.

00:35:14.420 --> 00:35:16.890
So basically, in order to run
away with the money, you need

00:35:16.890 --> 00:35:20.200
to dismantle the shop and then
take it, move away somewhere.

00:35:20.200 --> 00:35:23.370
So you need to try to move the
capital, so that's on the

00:35:23.370 --> 00:35:26.650
entire shop you need
to pay the cost.

00:35:26.650 --> 00:35:29.340
And that's some cost, h.

00:35:29.340 --> 00:35:31.840
And then suppose that you need
to pay some money to your

00:35:31.840 --> 00:35:32.540
depositors.

00:35:32.540 --> 00:35:35.510
So the cost of capital is
D, low cost of capital.

00:35:35.510 --> 00:35:39.530
So if you're the moneylender,
if he gets 1 in capital, he

00:35:39.530 --> 00:35:44.680
needs to repay D times 1
at the end of the day.

00:35:44.680 --> 00:35:48.400
So let's look at the
borrower choice.

00:35:48.400 --> 00:35:52.150
And the end, when he's realized
his money, he has a

00:35:52.150 --> 00:35:55.330
choice between repaying.

00:35:55.330 --> 00:35:59.560
So if he repays, he will get F
of k, which is what he's made

00:35:59.560 --> 00:36:04.320
with his business, minus K minus
w, what he has borrowed,

00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:08.540
multiplied by the interest rate,
growth interest rate.

00:36:08.540 --> 00:36:11.430
So that's if he decides
to behave.

00:36:11.430 --> 00:36:16.220
If he decides to run away, he
still gets F of k minus the

00:36:16.220 --> 00:36:17.970
cost of running away.

00:36:17.970 --> 00:36:19.730
Now what is the lender
going to do?

00:36:27.430 --> 00:36:29.670
At the end of the day, this
is the choice that

00:36:29.670 --> 00:36:31.200
the borrower has.

00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:33.669
What's the lender going to do?

00:36:33.669 --> 00:36:34.128
Ben?

00:36:34.128 --> 00:36:36.882
AUDIENCE: Make R times
k minus w term

00:36:36.882 --> 00:36:38.720
smaller than the hk term.

00:36:38.720 --> 00:36:39.040
PROFESSOR: Exactly.

00:36:39.040 --> 00:36:42.070
He's going to try to make
it worthwhile for

00:36:42.070 --> 00:36:42.890
the borrower to reimburse.

00:36:42.890 --> 00:36:51.402
So it's going to set R times k
minus w lower than hk, or at

00:36:51.402 --> 00:36:52.652
least equal.

00:36:56.830 --> 00:36:59.540
That is in order to make it
worth the while for the

00:36:59.540 --> 00:37:02.300
borrower to reimburse.

00:37:02.300 --> 00:37:04.470
So suppose we equalize that.

00:37:04.470 --> 00:37:09.020
We make R times k minus
w equal to h of k.

00:37:11.906 --> 00:37:14.940
That gives us the expression
that's over here, which is k

00:37:14.940 --> 00:37:19.780
over w is R times R minus h.

00:37:25.280 --> 00:37:29.700
It looks like it's almost
like a movie.

00:37:29.700 --> 00:37:34.110
Occasionally, some very, very
